org.mindswap.owls.process.execution
Interface ExecutionSupport<C extends ExecutionContext>

Type Parameters:
C - Any kind of context information required for executing one of the control constructs respectively process.
All Known Implementing Classes:
ProcessExecutionEngineImpl
public interface ExecutionSupport<C extends ExecutionContext>

This interface specifies the methods that need to be implemented for supporting execution of all control constructs specified by OWL-S as well as execution of all process types. It is intended to be implemented only by OWL-S execution engines. Furthermore, this interface is not intended to be accessible by clients that want to execute some service. In fact, the methods defined in this interface should be called only by the implementations of sub interfaces of ControlConstruct, c.f. ControlConstruct.execute(ExecutionContext, ExecutionSupport).

Note that control constructs can also be inspected via ControlConstructVisitor. This provides a general visitor pattern intended for public use (in contrast to this interface which is dedicated for execution engines).
